<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="settle-v">settle <strong><em>v</em></strong> ★</h1>
<p>英 /'setl/    美 /'setl/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.<strong>坐下；(使) 处于舒适的位置</strong></h4>
<p>to get into or put sb into a comfortable position：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The dog <strong>settled on</strong> the grass to enjoy its bone.
那条狗舒服地坐在草地上享受骨头的美味。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She <strong>settled herself into</strong> her chair and started to read.
她舒舒服服地坐在椅子上开始看书。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>(移民、殖民) 定居 (于)</strong></h4>
<p>to make a place your permanent home：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We <strong>settled</strong> happily <strong>into</strong> our new life in the town.
我们高兴地在那个镇上定居下来，开始了新的生活。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>This region was settled by the Dutch in the 19th century.
这个地区在19世纪开始有荷兰人定居。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>对某事达成一致意见；解决</strong></h4>
<p>to end an argument or solve a disagreement：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>settle an argument</strong>
解决争论</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Most of the problems have been settled satisfactorily.
大多数问题已得到满意的解决。</p></div>

<h4 id="4">4.★ <strong>[常用于被动语态] 确定；决定</strong></h4>
<p>to decide or arrange sth finally：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— When do you go to America?
你什么时候去美国？</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— Nothing’s settled yet.
一切待定。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>It was settled that</strong> they would get married in June.
他们决定于6月结婚。</p></div>

<h4 id="5">5.<strong>(使) 平静；(使) 安定</strong></h4>
<p>to become or make sb / sth become calm or quiet：</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She breathed deeply to <strong>settle</strong> her <strong>nerves</strong>.
她深呼吸来平复自己的紧张情绪。</p></div>

<h4 id="6">6.<strong>降落；停留：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>A butterfly <strong>settled on</strong> a red flower.
一只蝴蝶落在一朵红色的花上面。</p></div>

<h4 id="7">7.<strong>围绕；充满：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Depression <strong>settled over</strong> her like a heavy black cloud.
忧郁的情绪像一片乌云笼罩在她的心头。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="settle-back">settle back</h3>
<p>1.<strong>舒服地坐下 / 躺下：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She settled back in her seat to enjoy the film.
她舒服地坐在座位上看电影。</p></div>

<h3 id="settle-down">settle down</h3>
<p>1.★ <strong>舒适地坐下 / 躺下：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>They put up the tent, and settled down to eat the sandwiches.
他们搭起帐篷，舒服地坐下来享受三明治。</p><footer>2009 江西</footer></div>

<p>2.★ <strong>安顿下来；安定下来：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>When are you going to get married and settle down?
你打算什么时候结婚成家，安定下来啊？</p></div>

<p>3.★ <strong>(使) 安静；(使) 平静：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She didn’t start the lesson until the pupils settled down.
等学生们安静下来后，她才开始上课。</p></div>

<h3 id="settle-down-to">settle (down) to</h3>
<p>1.<strong>开始专心于；着手认真做：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>With so much noise outside, I couldn’t settle down to my work.
外面那么吵，我不能专心工作。</p></div>

<h3 id="settle-for">settle for</h3>
<p>1.<strong>勉强接受；将就：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She doesn’t settle for anything but the best.
她只想要最好的，绝不会将就。</p></div>

<h3 id="settle-in-into">settle in / into</h3>
<p>1.<strong>适应；习惯 (新事物)：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>How’s your new home? Are you settling in OK?
你的新家怎么样？你习惯吗？</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She soon settled into her new college life.
她很快就适应了大学的新生活。</p></div>

<h3 id="settle-on">settle on</h3>
<p>1.<strong>决定；选定</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We must settle on a place to meet.
我们得把见面的地点定下来。</p></div></div>